{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011imLvTwrXHax7RsSxTRvvF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: view-contract-enforcer\n     3→description: Enforce request-validation, permission, service-handoff, and response-contract boundaries in views without using jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# View Contract Enforcer (Control)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill when adding or updating API views.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `view_name`\n    13→- `http_method`\n    14→- `request_schema_name`\n    15→- `response_schema_name`\n    16→- `service_symbol`\n    17→- `url_path`\n    18→- `url_name`\n    19→- `test_name`\n    20→- `test_url`\n    21→\n    22→## Execution Checklist\n    23→\n    24→1. Validate input at the view boundary before business logic.\n    25→2. Keep authorization checks explicit and close to entrypoint behavior.\n    26→3. Hand domain writes to a service function (`service_symbol`), not the view.\n    27→4. Return a stable response contract (`response_schema_name`).\n    28→5. Add route and test coverage for the new view path.\n    29→\n    30→## Guardrails\n    31→\n    32→- No domain write logic in view functions.\n    33→- No ad hoc payload parsing that bypasses the request contract.\n    34→- Include both success and access/validation behavior in tests.\n    35→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c8b63b8-0524-46ad-a655-1f4ed1866de5","uuid":"a312c593-7eb5-407d-a1a3-abde906e3702"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Xgmfx2oAsSA7QaGs4jRBbr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The skill file is a benign checklist/spec document with no executable or malicious code.\n\nApplying the **view-contract-enforcer** checklist to the provided contract:\n\n**Contract Summary**\n- view_name: `entity_summary`\n- http_method: `POST`\n- request_schema_name: `EntitySummaryRequest`\n- response_schema_name: `EntitySummaryResponse`\n- service_symbol: `build_entity_summary`\n- url_path: `entities/<int:pk>/summary/`\n- url_name: `entity-summary`\n- test_name: `test_entity_summary`\n- test_url: `/api/entities/1/summary/`\n\n**Execution Checklist**\n\n1. **Validate input at the view boundary** — Parse `request.data` through `EntitySummaryRequest` before any business logic; reject invalid payloads with 400.\n2. **Explicit authorization** — Apply permission checks (e.g. `permission_classes` or explicit guard) at the view entrypoint, prior to service dispatch.\n3. **Service handoff** — View calls `build_entity_summary(pk=pk, payload=validated)`; no ORM writes or domain logic live in the view.\n4. **Stable response contract** — Serialize the service result through `EntitySummaryResponse` and return it; never return raw dicts or model instances.\n5. **Route + tests** — Register `path(\"entities/<int:pk>/summary/\", entity_summary, name=\"entity-summary\")`; add `test_entity_summary` hitting `/api/entities/1/summary/` via POST, covering success plus at least one validation and one access-denied case.\n\n**Guardrail Compliance**\n- No domain writes in `entity_summary` view — delegated to `build_entity_summary`.\n- No ad hoc payload parsing — all input flows through `EntitySummaryRequest`.\n- Test suite must include success, validation failure, and access/permission behavior.\n\nPer the project profile, this is a control run: checklist only, no code changes or `jig` execution performed."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":711,"cache_read_input_tokens":21718,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":711,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c8b63b8-0524-46ad-a655-1f4ed1866de5","uuid":"4589dbef-aa3e-4d49-bdca-003f9dd1aeca"}
